Weakness

What do you see as a significant weakness of this visualization? How could you improve it to make it clearer, easier to understand, or more impactful? Make sure you provide some detail in justifying your answer.


While I get the point of it, it was pretty hard for me to imagine how big 1ZB is from this visualization. From this visualization, I actually had to sort the information to conceptually understand the scale – by multiplying 1,000,000,000,000,000 from where it says in this visualization to create a 1ZB out of 1GB (or 1000^5), then I realized how big it is. The visualization had to show some comparative image from small to big to some extent even if not in the actual scale, so it may make easier for audience to understand the order of the units as well.

Strength

What do you see as a strength of this visualization? Is there a specific choice of the designer that made it especially useful or impactful? Make sure you provide some detail in justifying your answer.


I believe the points in each units count to 1000 and represent 1 unit of immediate smaller level, and we now know there are other units above terabyte (at least I wasn’t really that aware). It is a great way to create familiarity with the data units that may exist by now, and ensure there may come more to add in the future in this growing data world.
